		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=87"><span id=>jdwest</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>15 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=jdwest&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>OK, first, there a few problems with your goal and the way you are testing to reach your goal.&nbsp;&nbsp;To find out the best warrior vs. an NPC and the best warrior vs. a PC is something totally different.  VS. an NPC I lot of things will not matter, like being small and being able to hide and run around your opponent (especially if he is a big ogre and has trouble looking down and finding you).  The best warrior vs. an NPC is the one with the best equipment, the best leadership skills (as warriors often lead the battle), and the smartest fighter (no it DOES not make a BIG difference what race you are, sorry all your racists out there :) ).  I can elaborate further on these 3 points if you do not understand what I'm aiming for.  Now, that being said, the best warrior vs. an PC is one that knows how to best battle his opponent.  If he is a caster, you will put on your low delay weapons for max haste and best chance to interrupt spells, and bash the heck out of him.  You will also have to move well, so they cannot melee you (like constantly circling your opponent).  You also must focus on the caster and not the pet, as his spells will be what kills you, and not the limited damage of his pet.  I just started a character on Tallon Zek (Team PvP) named Dacrusher, and he is now a lvl 8 ogre.  I was EASILY able to be a shaman, a necro, and a mage of equal lvl because I KNEW how to take advantage of my enemies EVERY mistake.  Now, equipment matters here as well, but not near as much as it does vs. an NPC.  So what you SHOULD worry about is learning the best tactics for those dungeon/planes crawls, and get in good with those clerics/shamans/enchanters so you can get the best buffs, and know how to make the most money the fastest as possible so you can get the best equipment you can.  That's all there is to it :) .  I hope what I have written helps you to become a better warrior!</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Cuur Plunk<br>Ogre Myrmidon of the 56th Season<br>Terris Thule</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
